707610f-a.title: Manhattan: 1st Ave. - 46th St. E.
707610f-a.text:
First Avenue, east side, north across East 46th Street.
In the foreground is a semi-open frontage extending from
46th to 47th Street's. Note the meat smoking house to
the rear of same. The Beekman Towers (left) dominates
this locale.
July 23, 1939
September 28, 1940
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS

707612f-b.title: Manhattan: 1st Ave. - 46th St.
707612f-b.text:
(1)
First Avenue, east side, from 46th to 48th Streets, showing a filling
and service station from 46th to 47th Streets, where nine old five-
story tenement houses, 826-42 First Avenue, used to stand. Behind
the service station are old buildings belonging to Wilson \&
Company, packers; part of the Wilson slaughter house is shown
on the S.E. corner of 46th Street.
July 3, 1934.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
The same. Pirst Avenue at N.E. corner of 46th Street. Many filling
stations and garages on First Avenue in the I92O's.
